129
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,353
Pleace.
- And we hardly know each other.

130
00:13:13,439 --> 00:13:17,669
Show some hubris.
Come on, impress me.

131
00:13:18,017 --> 00:13:20,563
I bet it's huge.
- You have no idea.

132
00:13:20,649 --> 00:13:22,981
How big?

133
00:13:23,296 --> 00:13:27,327
What is it, this big? This big?
- I don't want to brag.

134
00:13:27,413 --> 00:13:29,381
Oh, come on! Come on.

135
00:13:29,467 --> 00:13:33,351
Let's just say I have a number in mind.
I haven't hit it yet.

136
00:13:36,492 --> 00:13:41,044
This is pretty fucking sexy.
- Hope it doesn't cheapen our relationship.

137
00:13:41,486 --> 00:13:45,606
We're two people who get turned on by Elite Status.
I think cheap is our starting point.

138
00:13:45,692 --> 00:13:49,327
There's nothing cheap about loyalty.

139
00:13:51,730 --> 00:13:56,662
We came up with this master plan,
which was for me...

140
00:13:56,748 --> 00:14:01,225
...to put gauze,
to put bandages on both my hands.

141
00:14:01,311 --> 00:14:06,967
Then we got on the plane,
transatlantic, flying to erm...Zurich.

142
00:14:07,053 --> 00:14:11,705
I waited till it was dark,
and I walked up to the bathroom with her.

143
00:14:11,791 --> 00:14:14,514
Everybody was watching the movie and I was like...

144
00:14:14,678 --> 00:14:20,041
Opened up, went inside. She opened the door for me,
and came in like she was gonna help me.

145
00:14:20,127 --> 00:14:24,150
We gave it our best shot. It wasn't
great. But it was fun. It was tricky.

146
00:14:24,236 --> 00:14:27,275
Give me some details.
- It's not so easy. Have you tried it?

147
00:14:27,361 --> 00:14:30,357
It's not so easy.
- Yes, I have.

148
00:14:31,019 --> 00:14:34,148
Really?
- Really.

149
00:14:38,638 --> 00:14:41,089
You've done that?
- I have done that.

150
00:14:41,175 --> 00:14:45,789
On a transatlantic flight?
- On a domestic flight - regional, actually.

151
00:14:45,875 --> 00:14:48,944
At night-time?
- Daytime.

152
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:51,088
What?
- How do you do that?

153
00:14:51,174 --> 00:14:54,513
Oh, I'm really flexible.

154
00:14:57,584 --> 00:15:01,121
Look. Ohh.

155
00:15:04,492 --> 00:15:07,953
Ah, I should throw these out.

156
00:15:11,116 --> 00:15:13,314
We can always use that room
with the ice machine.

157
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,577
Look.

158
00:15:31,118 --> 00:15:33,373
Good call on that towel rack.

159
00:15:33,459 --> 00:15:35,806
I like how you burritoed me
in the sofa cushions.

160
00:15:35,892 --> 00:15:37,635
I was improvising.

161
00:15:37,721 --> 00:15:41,258
Shame we didn't make it to the closet.

162
00:15:41,749 --> 00:15:44,938
We got to do this again.
- Oh, yeah.

163
00:15:49,179 --> 00:15:53,750
I'm in Newark on the 12th,
Modesto on the 13th...

164
00:15:53,836 --> 00:15:55,997
Oklahoma City on the 15th...

165
00:15:56,083 --> 00:15:59,588
Any Southwest? I'll be swinging by
Albuquerque week of the 16th.

166
00:15:59,674 --> 00:16:02,710
No, I'm in Florida on the 20th.
- Fort Lauderdale?

167
00:16:02,796 --> 00:16:06,593
Miami.
- That's nothing. - 40 minutes.

168
00:16:16,008 --> 00:16:19,414
I should probably go back to my room
so I can wake up in my bed.

169
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:22,617
I think that would be
the ladylike thing to do.

170
00:16:30,038 --> 00:16:34,401
Nice meeting you.
- A pleasure.

171
00:17:08,008 --> 00:17:09,248
Hello?

172
00:17:09,334 --> 00:17:10,916
<i>Hey, Ryan, how you holding up?</i>

173
00:17:11,002 --> 00:17:14,559
<i>Every family has one person
who keeps the genealogy in check.</i>

174
00:17:14,645 --> 00:17:17,342
<i>That's my sister Kara - the glue.</i>

175
00:17:17,428 --> 00:17:20,023
Fine. You and the kids?

176
00:17:20,109 --> 00:17:23,817
Missy's outstanding,
Matthew made varsity. How's the road?

177
00:17:23,903 --> 00:17:24,915
Couldn't be better.

178
00:17:25,001 --> 00:17:26,994
<i>Good. So, Ryan?</i>

179
00:17:27,080 --> 00:17:28,411
Yeah?

180
00:17:28,497 --> 00:17:33,521
I didn't even want to ask you this, because I know
how you are about doing things for others.

181
00:17:33,607 --> 00:17:37,911
But we're coming up on three weeks to go to
Julie's wedding and we could really use your help.

182
00:17:37,997 --> 00:17:39,121
Yeah?

183
00:17:39,207 --> 00:17:40,929
<i>We've been sending people these kits,</i>

184
00:17:41,015 --> 00:17:43,677
<i>so they can print out photos
of Julie and Jim on cardbord,</i>

185
00:17:43,763 --> 00:17:48,003
and then take photos of them in interesting places,
like that gnome in the French movie.

186
00:17:48,089 --> 00:17:49,792
Why?

187
00:17:49,878 --> 00:17:53,509
Because it's Julie's wedding and she thinks
it would be fun. Does it matter why?

188
00:17:53,595 --> 00:17:54,709
How is Julie?

189
00:17:54,795 --> 00:17:56,801
<i>Would you call her.
She thinks you've turned to butter.</i>

190
00:17:56,887 --> 00:18:00,839
You're awfully isolated how you live.
- Isolated? I'm surrounded.

191
00:18:00,925 --> 00:18:03,267
<i>So your assistant said
you were gonna be in Vegas.</i>

192
00:18:03,353 --> 00:18:04,413
Did he?

193
00:18:04,499 --> 00:18:08,342
Can you get a photo of the cut-out
in front of the Luxor pyramid?

194
00:18:08,428 --> 00:18:11,104
The place is a shithole.
Nobody stays there.

195
00:18:11,190 --> 00:18:16,363
Jesus, Ryan, I'm not asking you to check in.
Can you just take a stupid photo?

196
00:18:16,536 --> 00:18:18,067
I'll try my best.

197
00:18:18,153 --> 00:18:21,772
<i>Thank you for trying your best.</i>

198
00:18:39,553 --> 00:18:43,019
<i>Last year,
I spent 322 days on the road,</i>

199
00:18:43,105 --> 00:18:47,730
<i>which means I had to spend
43 miserable days at home.</i>

200
00:19:11,072 --> 00:19:13,076
Hey, neighbour.

201
00:19:16,433 --> 00:19:20,157
I signed for this while you were gone.
- Oh, thanks.

202
00:19:20,512 --> 00:19:24,097
I hope it wasn't too much of a bother.
- Nah.

203
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:33,148
It's my sister. I haven't met the guy yet.
They're getting married.

204
00:19:33,234 --> 00:19:35,353
Lots of luck.
- I know, right?

205
00:19:35,439 --> 00:19:39,988
What are you doing tonight?
You wanna come over later?

206
00:19:41,976 --> 00:19:44,280
Um...I've started seeing somebody.

207
00:19:44,366 --> 00:19:47,637
Oh. OK. Great.

208
00:19:48,042 --> 00:19:50,571
Hey, it's good to see you.

209
00:19:50,657 --> 00:19:54,407
You too.
- It seems like it's been a while this time.

210
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:15,965
I'm thrilled that everyone's back
under one roof. Welcome home, boy's.

211
00:20:16,051 --> 00:20:19,015
There's been a lot of whispering about
why we're here, so let me jump right in.

212
00:20:19,101 --> 00:20:22,611
Retailers are down 20%.

213
00:20:22,697 --> 00:20:27,267
Auto industry is in the dump.
Housing market doesn't have a heartbeat.

214
00:20:27,353 --> 00:20:31,704
It is one of the worst times on record
for America.

215
00:20:31,931 --> 00:20:35,257
This is our moment.

216
00:20:36,101 --> 00:20:40,565
Now, last summer, we received
a dynamite young woman here from Cornell.

217
00:20:40,651 --> 00:20:44,477
And she had some pretty big ideas
that she challenged me with.

218
00:20:44,563 --> 00:20:46,887
My first reaction was,
"Who does this kid think she is?"

219
00:20:46,973 --> 00:20:49,719
But after I gave it a listen,
she really knocked me out. So...

220
00:20:49,805 --> 00:20:54,610
With a peek into our future,
Natalie Keener.

221
00:20:56,309 --> 00:21:00,967
If there's one word I want to
leave you with today, it's this.

222
00:21:02,356 --> 00:21:04,715
